-Testing is how we find people with the virus and trace their contacts.

2) Surge/flex: Strengthen the healthcare system
3) Test/trace: Need federal partnership
4) Phased return — not all at once

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text: Holding a briefing with updates on #Coronavirus. WATCH LIVE: https://t.co/ji3FX8bXbf

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
I am alarmed by the reported increase in domestic violence incidents.

NYS wants you to know: You are not trapped because of #Coronavirus.

The State will help you find safe shelter.

Call 1-800-942-6906 if you need help. https://t.co/wQUxNivtAp

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text: I will be giving my daily #Coronavirus briefing at 12:00PM. Stay tuned.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text: RT @NYGovCuomo: Holding a briefing with updates on #Coronavirus. WATCH LIVE: https://t.co/gLjk74Ghtt

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
Every day we ask our healthcare system to do the impossible.

They pull off miracles daily to balance patient loads and supplies.

Thank you to the hospital administrators and thank you especially & profusely to the frontline healthcare workers.

Your service is awe-inspiring.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
This virus is an effective killer.

The vulnerable must be protected.

That’s why we are all #StayingHome.

Not only for us — but to protect the lives of others.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text: Holding a briefing with updates on #Coronavirus. WATCH LIVE: https://t.co/gLjk74Ghtt

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text: I will be giving my daily #Coronavirus briefing at 11:00AM. Stay tuned.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
NEW: The @NBA is contributing 1 million desperately needed surgical masks for New York's essential workers in collaboration with @nyknicks, @BrooklynNets and China's Consul General Huang Ping.

New York thanks you.

We are beyond grateful for this gift of critically needed PPE.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
I will be signing an Executive Order to allow medical students who were slated to graduate this spring to begin practicing now. 

These are extraordinary times and New York needs the help.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
The state of Oregon is sending 140 ventilators to NY. 

We are so grateful to @OregonGovBrown and the people of Oregon.

On behalf of the people of NY, I thank you and rest assured that NY will repay the favor when Oregon needs it.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
We finally got some good news today.

The Chinese government helped facilitate a donation of 1,000 ventilators that will arrive in JFK today.

I thank the Chinese government, Jack Ma, Joe Tsai, the Jack Ma Foundation, the Tsai Foundation and Consul General Huang.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
The Federal Government will staff and equip 2,500 beds in Javits for COVID patients.

This is a dramatic help in our battle against time, spread and lacking hospital capacity.

Reducing the strain on NYC area hospitals is a top priority.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text: Holding a briefing with updates on #Coronavirus. WATCH LIVE: https://t.co/fwFQbV1ZLE

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text: I will be giving my daily #Coronavirus briefing at 11:00AM. Stay tuned.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
How well we stay apart will directly impact the outcome of this pandemic.

Social distancing saves lives.

Spread the word. #NewYorkTough https://t.co/E1E0qg8qZO

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
There has been an uptick in domestic violence incidents.

We want you to know: If you are in a dangerous domestic situation NYS will help you find a safe shelter.

You are not trapped just because of #Coronavirus.


If you need help, call 1-800-942-6906.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
Helping one another is in the American DNA. 

When I put out the call, 20,000 out-of-state health professionals volunteered to come to NY.

We thank you.

At this time when we’re dealing with our worst let’s deploy America at its best.

Enlist: https://t.co/hr8dG89QK2

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
This virus is not an issue of states’ rights.

This is a national disaster.

The states need federal assistance. No state can get all the ventilators they need.

We need a national deployment of resources that follows need.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
We do not have enough ventilators. 

Period.

I am signing an Executive Order allowing the state to take ventilators and redistribute to hospitals in need.

The National Guard will be mobilized to move ventilators to where they are urgently required to save lives.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
Javits has now been converted and will receive COVID-19 patients. That adds 2,500 critically needed beds.

We made this request to the federal government, and I thank them for granting it.

We will do everything in our power to save lives.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
We need more supplies.

We need your help.

If you can manufacture PPE I urge you to do so. New York can offer funding.

Email Covid19supplies@esd.ny.gov

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text: In Albany giving the latest updates on #Coronavirus. WATCH: https://t.co/mE4fy8cVTp

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text: I will be giving my daily #Coronavirus briefing at 11:00AM. Stay tuned.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
This virus will roll across the country like a slow moving hurricane.

No state can stand alone. We need to jointly rush in and help where the need is.

I believe our nation will come together because it’s the only way to save lives.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
Special Enrollment for health insurance on @NYStateofHealth is extended until May 15.

If you lost your job-based health coverage, or you're uninsured, enroll today.

The NYS health marketplace is open.
https://t.co/xGDrEyGVzc

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
Happening soon: I will be on @maddow on MSNBC at 9pm.

At 9:20pm I’m joining @CNN's #Coronavirus Town Hall with @AndersonCooper and @DrSanjayGupta. Tune in.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
•Outlaws 'Pink Tax'
•Bans flavored e-cigarettes
•Cuts middle class taxes
•Safely legalizes e-bikes & e-scooters
•Prohibits individuals who commit serious offenses in other states from obtaining NY gun license

More: https://t.co/VwNJsuH1UC
#NewYorkTough

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text: #BREAKING: The President just approved our request to use the temporary hospital facility at the Javits Center to care for COVID-19 patients. https://t.co/VMtvCpzkPo

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text: Social distancing saves lives. #NewYorkTough https://t.co/Qx5gCy6IoA

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
I asked Chris to join us this morning. 

Christopher is fighting hard.

I’m so proud of him for showing New York what this vicious virus looks like and for demystifying it.

Love you, little brother. #NewYorkTough https://t.co/NjSWEbBnU9

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
1. We are using anesthesia machines as ventilators.

2. We are "splitting" ventilator tubes so two patients can share a ventilator.

3. We are converting BiPAP machines into ventilators.

4. We are scouring the globe to acquire more ventilators.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
Last night we released 600 ventilators to NYC, Long Island and Westchester.

We have 6 days of ventilators left in our stockpile at the current burn rate.

We are taking extraordinary measures to move ventilators to meet the need.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
We need supplies. 

We need your help.

If you can manufacture PPE I implore you to do so. NYS will pay a premium.

Email Covid19supplies@esd.ny.gov

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
Every county in New York has now reported a Coronavirus case.

This virus has marched across our state.

We have counties with more cows than people. That didn’t stop it.

Urban, suburban, and rural: We're all affected.

It will march across our nation next.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text: Holding a briefing with updates on #Coronavirus. WATCH LIVE: https://t.co/i28pCmvHco

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text: I will be giving my daily #Coronavirus briefing at 11:30AM. Stay tuned.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
NEW: @Apple has donated 1.9 million masks to the State of New York with more on the way.

We are so grateful to Apple for this much-needed gift of critical PPE supplies.

Thank you. Thank you.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
Increased testing is desperately needed.

Regeneron is donating 500,000 test kits to New York free of charge.

We got the first batch on Monday.

Thank you, @Regeneron.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
How many people have to die before the people ignoring social distancing get that they have a responsibility?

One person sneezes — another person gets intubated.

We all have to look out for each other.

STAY HOME. SAVE LIVES.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
We are all vulnerable to this virus.

I couldn’t protect my little brother. He couldn’t protect himself. And it's scary.

I'm worried about him just as we are all worried about the people we love.

I love you, little brother. Stay strong.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
Density is still too high and is still too dangerous.

We are closing the NYC playgrounds because they are too crowded.

Open spaces will remain open for fresh air and sun. 

Stay six feet apart. Stop the spread.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
How bad will this pandemic be?

One of the main variables is how effective social distancing is.

That means YOU can influence the outcome.

Stay Home. Save Lives.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
Geography won't help you.

Rural areas are not immune.

Just as rural New York has been impacted, so will rural America.

This virus affects us all.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text: Holding a briefing with updates on #Coronavirus. WATCH LIVE: https://t.co/Bvs0I7XYfi

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text: I will be giving my daily #Coronavirus briefing at 12:00PM. Stay tuned.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
The mental health impact of this pandemic is very real.

New York is here to help.

Get free emotional support, consultation, and referral to a provider.

Call the State's Emotional Support Hotline at 1-844-863-9314

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
This virus is insidious. It's my family, it's your family.

Don't ignore social distancing directives.

Your actions don't just impact you — they impact the people around you. https://t.co/McS3JYZ1yY

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
This virus is the great equalizer.

Stay strong little brother. You are a sweet, beautiful guy and my best friend.

If anyone is #NewYorkTough it’s you. https://t.co/B7veuweZzx

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
We are creating a Central Coordinating Team led by the State Department of Health.

It will organize upstate-to-downstate staffing needs.

It will organize patient transfers between hospitals.

It will also organize transfers to the USNS Comfort.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
Our healthcare system is a chain. If one link breaks the whole chain breaks.

Our hospitals must function as one system.

The distinction between private and public, upstate and downstate needs to end.

New York is one state. In New York we stand together.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
We must support our healthcare professionals. 

They are the frontline.

They are physically and emotionally exhausted and they need relief.

We are asking for more volunteers to join our surge healthcare force.

Enlist now: https://t.co/hr8dG89QK2

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
We have two missions:

One is on the front lines in our hospitals.

The second is the battle to get all New Yorkers to stay home.

Stay home. Stop the Spread. Do it.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text: Holding a briefing with updates on #Coronavirus. WATCH LIVE: https://t.co/iTt5ZlaTmD

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text: I will be giving my daily #Coronavirus briefing at 11:30 AM. Stay tuned.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
Today is #EqualPayDay.

Never has it been more urgent to close the gender pay gap.

Women are on the front lines, risking their health, safety and lives and that of their families in the battle against Coronavirus.

They deserve equal pay. Period.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text: RT @EsteeLauder: We're donating two million surgical masks for those on the front lines in New York as part of our efforts toward COVID-19…

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
Right now healthcare professionals are risking their lives.

We are all in their debt.

They deserve to have every piece of equipment they need to do their job — it's the least we can do. https://t.co/DnweX9sECO

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
The best way to thank our doctors and healthcare professionals is to listen to them.

Here's one doctor's message from the front line to his fellow New Yorkers:

#NationalDoctorsDay https://t.co/NimKDFSmAm

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
In this crisis we need all our hospitals — public and private — to work together.

They will be one cohesive system.

It is the only way to save lives.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
I am asking healthcare workers across the country:

If things are not urgent in your own community, please come to New York.

We need relief for nurses. We need relief for doctors. 

If you can, help us: https://t.co/hr8dG89QK2

We will return the favor in your hour of need.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
The key battle in this fight is taking place in hospitals across the city, the state and this country. 

Our healthcare workers are on the front line.

They are the soldiers fighting this battle on behalf of all of us.

Support them — stay home.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
No American is immune.

What is happening in New York is NOT an anomaly.

We will share the lessons learned here across this country. 

#COVID19

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text: At the Javits Center in New York City giving a briefing on #Coronavirus. WATCH: https://t.co/Zx7b6P8wag

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
New York is heartbroken by the death of Josef Neumann, who was brutally attacked during a Hanukkah celebration in Monsey three months ago.

This hate-motivated attack shook us to our core.

Any attack on one of us is an attack on all of us.
https://t.co/6sx3x9XhrT

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
Welcome to New York, @USNSComfort.

We knew from the outset that expanded hospital capacity was critical.

We asked and the federal government answered.

This ship is a step forward in our fight against Coronavirus. https://t.co/r6Hj8NL9JH

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
To each and every doctor putting his or her life at risk to save the lives of others, we thank you from the bottom of our hearts.

You are the unwavering front line soldiers, angels and heroes in this war.

You make New York proud.
#NationalDoctorsDay

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
RT @melissadderosa: There have been Q's on if our EO on childbirth extends to recovery

DOH's directive mandates allowing 1 support person…

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
NY wasn’t helped by the federal legislation. 

We received less than other states despite having the most COVID-19 cases. 

I spoke to Senators Schumer, Gillibrand & Speaker Pelosi & they have committed to right this wrong. 

I am committed to working with them.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
A new drive-thru #Coronavirus testing center is coming to the Bronx.

The facility will be in Co-Op City and opens Monday.

Residents MUST make an appointment by calling 888-364-3065.

Priority will go to higher-risk individuals.
@CarlHeastie @jamaaltbailey @mikebenedetto82

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
We're devastated by the death of Kious Kelly, a nurse manager at Mt. Sinai West, to coronavirus.

He and other medical staff show up every day to save lives. Tragically he lost his own doing so.

We can't thank our health care professionals enough for their selflessness & bravery

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
I'm heartbroken that New York lost Detective Cedric Dixon, a 23-year veteran from the 23rd @NYPD Precinct, to coronavirus.

Our first responders are risking their lives every day to protect the people of this state.

I do not have the words to express our gratitude to this hero.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text: Holding a briefing with updates on #Coronavirus. WATCH LIVE: https://t.co/Cz22UlT3aC

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
I'm deeply saddened that we have lost 728 New Yorkers to Coronavirus.

We are fighting to save every life. You must help by following all health protocols.

We ALL have a role to play to reduce the spread of this virus.

Help us save lives.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
We are working on three dedicated COVID-only hospitals.

We will prepare 600+ beds for the treatment of coronavirus patients.

It is the safest thing to do.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
NEW: We will move our presidential primary to June 23rd.

Public health is our number one priority and we will carry out this vital democratic process at a safer date.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
There is a concern that the CDC guidelines on PPE are not adequately protecting our nurses & doctors.

We're aware of the concerns & we're actively looking into it.

If the guidelines don’t sufficiently protect our health care professionals, we'll put our own guidelines in place.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
In projections we trust.

For projections we plan.

Accordingly we need 30,000 ventilators.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
Every emergency is unique.

Needs are always different. 

The only similarity is that what is needed is always unexpected.

In this case the unexpected need is ventilators.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text: Holding a briefing with updates on #Coronavirus. WATCH LIVE: https://t.co/EoOAi1pZsr

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
A Special Enrollment Period is now open on the @NYStateofHealth marketplace.

If you are uninsured or if you recently lost employer coverage, apply for a health plan today:
https://t.co/xGDrEyGVzc

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
We desperately needed the Defense Production Act invoked to ensure the production of life-saving ventilators.

We are relieved that just happened.

Lives depend on it.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
New York still needs qualified healthcare professionals, including retirees, to join the state's surge healthcare force.

Enlist at https://t.co/hr8dG89QK2

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
I hope NY doesn’t ultimately need 30,000 ventilators.

But I don't operate on opinion and hope.

I operate on facts and data and science.

All the projections say we will need 30,000-40,000 ventilators.

So that is what we will strive to have.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
New Yorkers never cease to amaze me. The outpouring of support is extraordinary.

62K medical staff have answered our call to help. 

Over 10K mental healthcare workers have answered our call to help.

When someone needs something, there’s no place I’d rather be than New York.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
We mourn the 519 New Yorkers lost to this vicious virus.

This is the worst news I can give New Yorkers. It is heartbreaking.

Sadly, we expect this number to rise as patients who have been on ventilators for weeks succumb.

We will keep fighting to save every life we can.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
With #COVID19 spreading quickly, our number one priority is expanding hospital capacity.

All NY hospitals are increasing capacity by 50%, some by 100%.

We have also identified 4 new temp hospital sites. 

One in the Bronx, one in Queens, one in Brooklyn & one in Staten Island.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
Schools will remain closed statewide until at least April 15 to reduce the spread of #COVID19. 

School districts will continue to provide childcare, meals and daily programming. 

We will reassess at that time.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text: At the Javits Center in New York City giving a briefing on #Coronavirus. WATCH: https://t.co/Fwj4LXm0vn

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
Our thoughts are with the family of the NYC Transit worker who tragically died in a fire early this morning, and with all those who are injured.

The NYPD is investigating the incident. I thank the firefighters and all first responders who bravely keep us safe every day.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
I want to thank @rihanna and the Rihanna Foundation for donating Personal Protective Equipment to New York State.

We're so appreciative of your help and that of so many others who have stepped up.

5/5

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
Thank you to:

-The Office of @NewYorkStateAG for protective masks and gloves
-The Commission on Independent Colleges and Universities in NY (@CICU) for ventilators and PPE
-JUDY for N-95 masks
-@Huawei for N-95 masks, isolation gowns, medical goggles and gloves

4/5

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
Thank you to:

-@Niagara_Water for bottles of water
-@AmnealPharma for Hydroxychloroquine
-Long Island Ambulatory Surgery Center for a ventilator
-@Uniqlo for masks
-@Corning Life Sciences for centrifuge tubes and cryovials
-@NBCUniversal for medical supplies and PPE

3/5

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
Thank you to:

-@SuburbanPropane for propane services
-@GoldmanSachs for masks
-@Wayfair for mattresses, linens, sheets & pillows for field hospitals
-@Walmart for use of parking lots & store facilities infrastructure
-@Keurig/@drpepper for coffee/beverages for volunteers

2/5

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
New York is fighting a war against this virus and we need all the help we can get.

On behalf of the family of New York, I'm deeply grateful to:

-@BollandBranch for hospital mattresses
-@Restore_Global for coveralls
-@Facebook and @Loreal for hand sanitizer

1/5

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
Stay informed.

Get nightly updates with critical information on the #Coronavirus pandemic and New York’s response: https://t.co/4VJqk8OBlz
https://t.co/D0CPq9mWV3

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
This is not a sprint—it's a marathon.

I know NYers are tired. I’m tired too.

But when I feel tired, I think of the healthcare professionals working 7-day weeks.

I think of the first responders showing up every day.

I think of the pharmacists, transit workers & so many others.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
We mourn the 385 New Yorkers we have lost to Coronavirus-related illnesses.

Tragically, we expect the number to rise as many patients have been on ventilators for weeks. 

NY will keep fighting flat out to save lives. 

Help us save lives by staying home.

#NewYorkTough

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
New York is doing more tests, now up to 18,650 tests per day.

25% of all tests in the country have been done in New York.

We need to find the positives to help stop the spread.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
We want to see a reduction in rate of increase of spread. That's the first sign of progress.

We are doing everything possible to slow the spread while adding hospital capacity.

Our goal is to have a 1000+ overflow facility in every county.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text: Holding a briefing with updates on #Coronavirus. WATCH LIVE: https://t.co/9pTnNjROON

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
The best way to thank our nurses and health care workers is to listen to them.

Here’s one ICU nurse‘s plea to her fellow New Yorkers.

#NewYorkTough https://t.co/e8nHYGIvQQ

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
NEW: @SoftBank donated 1.4 million critically needed N-95 masks to us.

New York State thanks you.

We are so grateful for this PPE that protects our healthcare workers.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
Grateful for the heroes who are stepping up for all of us.

Thank you to every:

-EMT
-Nurse
-Doctor
-Store clerk
-Police officer
-Mental health worker
-Firefighter
-Transit worker
-Childcare worker
-Mail carrier
-Takeout cook
-Deliverer
-Teacher

And many, many more.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
The Four Seasons Hotel on 57th Street will provide FREE lodging to doctors, nurses & medical personnel currently working to respond to the #COVID19 pandemic.

Thank you @FourSeasons. 

The first of many hotels we hope will make their rooms available.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
In NY we are concerned about the mental health part of this pandemic, too.

We can’t underestimate that.

For FREE emotional support, consultation, and referral to a provider, call 1-844-863-9314

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
This is not binary.

We can advance a public health strategy that is also an intelligent economic strategy.

But the first order of business? Save lives.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
Every state will have a different apex with this virus. New York is first.

I told the White House, send us the equipment we need. Then we will deploy it to the states that come after us.

I personally guarantee it.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
Our single greatest challenge is ventilators.

We need 30,000 ventilators.

We have 11,000.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
Evidence suggests density control plan may be working:

On Sun, hospitalizations doubling every 2 days
On Mon, hospitalizations doubling ever 3.4 days
On Tues, hospitalizations doubling every 4.7 days

But the virus is STILL spreading quickly. #StayAtHome

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text: Holding a briefing with updates on #Coronavirus. WATCH LIVE: https://t.co/Z3IdQirL3Y

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
Thank you @nyuniversity. It's all hands on deck.

New York is calling on qualified health care professionals to join our health care reserve. 

Enlist here: https://t.co/aogtjOWEFP https://t.co/Z9Hm0TrXNT

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
We are not willing to sacrifice 1-2% of New Yorkers.

That’s not who we are.

We will fight to save every life we can.

I am not giving up.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
My mother is not expendable. Your mother is not expendable.

We will not put a dollar figure on human life. 

We can have a public health strategy that is consistent with an economic one.

No one should be talking about social darwinism for the sake of the stock market.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
The federal government must distribute ventilators based on need.

We need them in New York NOW.

After New York gets past the apex of this pandemic, I will transport the ventilators myself wherever they are next needed.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
I do not understand the reluctance to use the federal Defense Production Act to manufacture ventilators. 

If not now, when?

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
New York needs 30,000 ventilators.

It will be the difference between life and death.

The federal government must provide these ventilators.
 
Only the federal government has the power to deliver.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
The apex of this pandemic is higher & sooner than we thought. 

We believe we are 14-21 days away from this apex.

We are scaling hospital capacity as fast as humanly possible.

I will turn this state upside down to get the hospital beds we need.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
We had projected a need for 110K hospital beds at the apex of this virus.

The rate of infection is INCREASING and the curve has increased.

New projections show we may need 140K beds.

NYS is doing everything we can on every level to slow the spread.

We need your cooperation.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
If it’s public health versus the economy, the only choice is public health. You cannot put a value on human life.

You do the right thing. That’s what Pop taught us @ChrisCuomo

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
Prepare for the worst, hope for the best.

Public Health comes first. https://t.co/EbWeJyYOgR

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
Toured the Javits Center today where FEMA has started work on a 1,000-bed temporary hospital to open next week.

Equipment from both the state & federal government is being delivered here.

My thanks go to everyone working so hard to make this happen so quickly. https://t.co/4gStus7TUo

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
NYS put out a call for retired healthcare professionals to enlist in NY's #Coronavirus response.

We also called on qualified medical & nursing school students to enlist.

I'm proud that 30,000 people have responded.

We still need more! Enlist now: https://t.co/hr8dG89QK2

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
On Tuesday New York is beginning FDA-approved drug trials for very sick #Coronavirus patients.

The FDA also approved @HealthNYGov to proceed with a trial of an experimental antibody therapy on a compassionate care basis.

We are fighting this virus in every way.

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text: Holding a briefing with updates on #Coronavirus. WATCH LIVE: https://t.co/C33knOoLIp

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
New York is a community. That means we rely on each other.

We ALL need to practice social distancing.

That's part of the social contract, especially now when it counts.

Help your community! #StayAtHome https://t.co/78Nzv4TARd

Name: Andrew Cuomo
Text:
I’m calling on the Federal Government to nationalize the medical supply chain.

The Federal Government should immediately use the Defense Production Act to order companies to make gowns, masks and gloves.
